sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Customer
    participant S as Sales Team
    participant F as Finance
    participant IT as IT Ops

    C->>S: Submit onboarding request
    S->>F: Credit check request
    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Risk assessment after credit check
    F->>F: Risk Assessment (Score >750, Verified Co., Clean History?)
    alt Low-Risk (all criteria met) - Expedited Path
        F-->>S: Auto-approved (low-risk bypass)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts (expedited)
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials (within 24h)
    else High-Risk - Standard Path
        F->>F: Route to Finance Director for approval
        F-->>S: Finance Director Approval (24h SLA)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials
    end
    %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION
    C->>IT: First login confirmation
    IT->>S: Onboarding complete
    S->>C: Kickoff meeting scheduled

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Added a risk assessment step within Finance after the credit check request. An alt/else block now branches the flow: low-risk customers (score >750, verified company status, clean payment history) receive auto-approval and proceed directly to expedited account provisioning, while high-risk customers follow the original path requiring explicit Finance Director approval before provisioning. The post-provisioning steps (first login, onboarding complete, kickoff scheduling) remain shared for both paths.